pullsbody:
This adds a Python extension module that wraps libprio with SWIG. This fixes issues that I was having with multi-processing, so it should be safe to call this within other libraries. I've tested this on macOS and linux.

I've done some testing in another branch, and can generate binary wheels for Python 3.8 on linux that can be installed on Ubuntu 20.04 (as long as nss, nspr, and msgpackc are available). 

